Competed in my final event of the year last weekend at the South Florida Open and walked away with the victory! 🥇 It's been a wild season,  but capping it off with a W is a sweet cherry on top. The people were kind, the courses were fun and the wildlife stalking was awesome…..so many iguanas! Enjoyed playing each round with my cardmates and getting to know some more Florida-based FPOs. Got treated to a practice round with @krisknauer and the amazing caddy skills of @discgolf_life12 . Always fun to play with @discprincess and @widboomshakalaka , as well as getting to know the Lynds' sisters, @morgantlynds & @jordan_lynds , whose games are on a steep rise! Follow @acerunpro for full coverage when it comes out. 
.
 Big thanks to all my friends and fans who've shown me so much love this year.  You all make this sport so special. Also, huge thanks to my sponsors, @mvpdiscsports , @paragondiscgolf @zucainc and @mittenbags . Y'all make the world go round for me and I'm ever grateful for our partnerships.
.
Training for 2023 starts TODAY!
.

Jonesboro was rough! 😕 My putting mechanics slowly de-volved throughout the weekend, all while memories of previous putting struggles invaded my brain. 🤯 I finished the event feeling completely dejected and missed the cash line. 🤦‍♀️ I didn't want to even look at a frisbee the next day. But, it only took a few focused practice sessions to whip my stroke back into shape and now I have a more robust toolbox for the next set of challenges. 💯 Thank you, disc golf, for the humble pie 🥧, followed by the confidence of overcoming once again. 💪 Congrats to @the_legit_kat on her first big one! 👏

I've had a truly fantastic week in Norway for the PCS Open. I finished in 5th place and felt my play was good overall, minus a few missed putts in the second round. Øverås Discgolfpark is a unique,  fun and challenging track that tests all the skills in your bag and required a true golfer’s mentality to navigate successfully. I’m also incredibly thankful that the decision was made to offer an FPO layout. This is not common in Europe and it was great to see this group take that important step for women’s disc golf and pave the way for others in this part of the world to do the same. Thank you to Jøran, Sivert, the DGPT and the army of volunteers who made this week very special and to the entire community for welcoming me to your beautiful land of fjords and mountains. Huge shout out to @camillafinnoy for caddying for me and to both her and Rob for the amazing times and ride to the airport. I had the last-minute opportunity to step into the commentary booth with @throw_like_lucky for @jomezpro post-production, so please check out the coverage and support their page. Also want to send some support to @ppierce29190 at this time as she deals with her very unfortunate injury. We were all thinking of her this weekend and wish her a speedy recovery. Finally, HUGE thanks to @mvpdiscsports for continuing to support me and giving me the opportunity to see the world while representing them on the course.  I wouldn’t be here without you! SKOL!
Next up, I travel to Finland to compete in the European Open for the first time since 2015.

Then, enjoyed cheering my USA teammates on to an exciting President's Cup victory today.  I've been able to get a few quality practice rounds completed and I am ready to battle The Beast.

 I tee off at 8:50am tomorrow (which is the middle of the night for the US), so if you can't tune in LIVE, catch me and @throw_like_lucky calling the shots on the @jomezpro post-production.

This controversy is bigger than disc golf. For us to take on the task of solving this ourselves puts the growth of the sport in jeopardy. While the United Series is not a perfect solution, it does ensure that FPO players can continue to pursue their dreams, travel with their significant others, and play on courses that have historic significance and strong community support, while still maintaining the view that bodies that went through male puberty make competition unfair in FPO. This also ensures that the DGPT is in compliance with state laws in regions that recognize gender identity and sex as identical. This challenging topic has ripped this sport in two and the United Series serves to allows disc golf to "tread water" on this topic, while larger sporting organizations (World Athletics, Cycling, NCAA, Olympics, etc) with much deeper pockets tackle the legal battles. Ultimately, I believe the courts will rule to ensure fairness in competition at all levels for females who did not undergo male puberty, but until those larger battles take place, the sport of disc golf will drown itself in the legal system and division within the community will widen if we don't find a way through this soon. While this is still a huge compromise most of the FPO does not want to make, but I think it's the best path forward at this time, so we can all get back to what we love... playing disc golf and creating positive connections with our communities and each other.

After a short hiatus,  I’m back to give ya'll a little season recap and an update. 

I got to finish my main season a few weeks ago with a win at the DGMT Finale at North Cove. Most important about that week was watching @callie_mcmorran_64751 dreams come alive and hardwork come to fruition. On top of that, being able to participate in the fun-packed week in a beautiful place with some of my favorite people made the finale superb! The rest of my season was a bit of a rollercoaster. I had a few good performances to start off, but also a few missed cashes sprinkled in. My game was progressing nicely through the middle of the season and I had good performances in Europe. As the season wore on I really started to feel the grind.  Just before Worlds I made some changes to my putt, which turned out to be terrible timing for a change like that,  but  I do like where it's at now , so…….My performances during playoffs and US womens were mediocre, but I was hopeful that the work I was putting in would pay off in the end.  Unfortunately, I severely rolled my ankle while competing in the Carolina Clash (an A tier event I was playing to prep for the DGPT Finale) and had to hobble through the Throw Pink event, DGPT and DGMT Finales. My ankle is still in treatment, but I'm hopeful for a full recovery by the start of next season. In the meantime,  I am still playing a bunch of A tiers in Florida, so I'm looking forward to re-connecting with the community down here. 

Huge thanks to my sponsors! MVP makes the best discs on the market and are just a solid bunch of humans. ZUCA has had my back (literally) for years and I love rolling my cart. Paragon is my go-to guy for anything disc golf and Mitten bags have had a big hand in keeping my grip intact. 

Also gotta shout out to my friends, family, fans and my #1 caddy/life caddy @zagonage. This life would be a lot less fun without you all.
